						<summary>

						<p>Above the natural cave at Aivarmalai.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">Pāṇḍya, Varaguṇa, Year 8 and Śaka, Year 792 = 870 A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>Vaṭṭeḻuttu. Records that Santivīrakuravar, pupil of Kunavīrakkuravaḍigaḷ, renovated the images of Pāriśvapaḍārar and <hi rend="italic">yakshis</hi> at Tiruvayirai and gave an endowment of 505 <hi rend="italic">kāṇam</hi> for two continuous offerings <hi rend="italic">(muṭṭāavi)</hi> and for feeding an ascetic.</p>						

						<p>[Published in <hi rend="italic">SII</hi>, XIV, No. 22.]</p>						

						</summary>
